    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-01-07T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-01-07T04:00:00-05:00" n="710"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d710">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/13333: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-01-07T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >January 7, 1936—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 7—10:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5. Consul General Hankow reported on December 30 that some anxiety is felt
                    concerning the safety of American Catholic missionaries at Chihkiang, Hunan
                    Province, and that he had made representations to the Provincial Government. The
                    following telegram has now been received from Josselyn: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“January 6, 3 p.m. Telegram received from Chihkiang by Catholic mission
                            Hankow, January 3rd states. ‘All safe.’ Changsha press reports January
                            5th that Reds who threatened Chihkiang had moved into Kweichow by way of
                            Hwanghsien and were near Tungjen, Kweichow, on January 3rd and that Reds
                            in Suining district are moving past Tsinghsien towards Kweichow
                            border.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
